{"id":32807,"title":"Patellofemoral ligament reconstruction in a patient with Rubinstein-Taybi syndrome.","abstract":"Recurrent dislocation of patella may occur in patients with ligament laxity. Method of treatment in this condition is controversial but patellofemoral ligament reconstruction is the most accepted method. We present a patient with Rubinstein-Taybi syndrome and recurrent patellar dislocation who managed successfully by patellofemoral ligament reconstruction. ","date":"2014-06-06","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24901727","annotations":[{"name":"Patient","weight":0.418934,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Ligament","weight":0.0546925,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ligament"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Patella","weight":0.0334927,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patella"},{"name":"Ligamentous laxity","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ligamentous_laxity"},{"name":"Joint dislocation","weight":0.0265917,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joint_dislocation"},{"name":"Recurrent neural network","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recurrent_neural_network"},{"name":"Reconstructive plastic surgery","weight":0.0162839,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reconstructive_plastic_surgery"},{"name":"Syndrome","weight":0.015901,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syndrome"},{"name":"Controversy","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Controversy"},{"name":"Management","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Management"}]}
